snippet.textDisplay:
However this ends, one thing is for sure.
Australia will never be able to wash away this shame.
Politicians have turned the country into a prison. While criminals roam the country freely, an innocent man is detained and expelled, who does not pose any danger to human health.
I would like the Australians to direct their justified anger to the right address, and that address is certainly not Novak.
Give the sport back to the athletes.
Limit the influence of politicians, where they do not belong.
Behind their supposed health care lies a desire for total control and power.
